Occidental Petroleum Corporation (Oxy) is an American multinational oil and gas exploration and production company with operations in the United States, the Middle East, and Latin America.[4] Headquartered in Houston, Texas,[5] it is one of the largest American oil and gas companies based on 2015 year-end market capitalization.[6] Often abbreviated as "Oxy", in reference to its ticker symbol, the company is ranked on the Forbes Global 2000[5] and Fortune 500 list.[7] In 2015, it was the 16th largest gas producer[8] and 3rd largest oil producer in Texas.[9]



